"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911213","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Home Office does not centrally hold the information requested.</p><p>From April 2017 the Home Office has requested information on a voluntary basis from the police on the number of individuals released on pre-charge bail, broken down by bail length. It is intended that these data will be published for the first time in Autumn 2018. However, these data will not contain information on the offence group.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","147969","2018-06-04T15:50:15.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911213/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911213/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911213/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Bail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police applications for pre-charge bail have been made for (a) drug offences, (b) rape charges, (c) firearms offences, (d) other dangerous weapon offences, (e) grievous bodily harm, (f) manslaughter, (g) murder and (h) all other offences in (i) Derbyshire and (ii) each region of the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","147967"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911214","Attorney General","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) does not collect data on the number of applications made by the CPS to the courts to extend custody time limits or on applications made by the CPS to the court to extend pre-charge bail periods. Such information could only be obtained through a manual search of records which would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2018-06-04T07:52:33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911214/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911214/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911214/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-05-24","Bail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many CPS applications to extend the custody time limit for bail have been made for (a) drug offences, (b) rape charges, (c) firearms offences, (d) other dangerous weapon offences, (e) grievous bodily harm, (f) manslaughter, (g) murder and (h) all other offences in (i) Derbyshire and (ii) each region of the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","147968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911215","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Home Office does not centrally hold the information requested.</p><p>From April 2017 the Home Office has requested information on a voluntary basis from the police on the number of individuals released on pre-charge bail, broken down by bail length. It is intended that these data will be published for the first time in Autumn 2018. However, these data will not contain information on the offence group.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","147967","2018-06-04T15:50:15.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911215/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911215/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911215/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Bail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many successful police applications for pre-charge bail have been made for (a) drug offences, (b) rape charges, (c) firearms offences, (d) other dangerous weapon offences, (e) grievous bodily harm, (f) manslaughter, (g) murder and (h) all other offences in (i) Derbyshire and (ii) each region of the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","147969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911216","Attorney General","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) does not collect data on the outcome of applications made by the CPS to the courts to extend custody time limits or the outcome of applications made by the CPS to the court to extend pre-charge bail periods. Such information could only be obtained through a manual search of records which would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2018-06-04T07:57:39.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911216/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911216/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911216/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-05-24","Bail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many successful CPS applications to extend the custody time limit for bail have been made for (a) drug offences, (b) rape charges, (c) firearms offences, (d) other dangerous weapon offences, (e) grievous bodily harm, (f) manslaughter, (g) murder and (h) all other offences in (i) Derbyshire and (ii) each region on the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","147970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911217","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Department held a consultation exercise between 17 February 2018 and 16 April 2018 on electrical safety in the private rented sector. We received 582 responses which are currently being analysed and expect to publish the Government’s response in the Autumn.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-06-04T11:23:18.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911217/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911217/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911217/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-24","Private Rented Housing: Electrical Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what representations his Department has received in opposition to mandatory electrical safety checks in the private rented sector.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","147943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911218","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Department received a total of 582 responses to the recent consultation on electrical safety in the private rented sector, of which 45 were from local authorities.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-06-04T11:19:41.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911218/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911218/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911218/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-24","Private Rented Housing: Electrical Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what representations his Department has received from local authorities regarding mandatory electrical safety checks in the private rented sector.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","147944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911219","Department for Education","false","2018-06-08","<p>The number of black students achieving[1] three A*-A grades at A level[2], split by ethnic group, from 2010/11 – 2016/17[3] are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Academic year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of students</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number achieving three A*-A grades</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010/11</strong></p></td><td><p>8,989</p></td><td><p>358</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011/12</strong></p></td><td><p>9,415</p></td><td><p>343</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012/13</strong></p></td><td><p>10,385</p></td><td><p>407</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013/14</strong></p></td><td><p>10,622</p></td><td><p>400</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014/15</strong></p></td><td><p>11,411</p></td><td><p>459</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p>9,457</p></td><td><p>449</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2016/17<strong>[4]</strong></strong></p></td><td><p>9,234</p></td><td><p>487</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Figures for 2009/10 are not readily available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>[1] Based on students at the end of their 16-18 study.</p><p>[2] Based on students who entered for at least 1 A level or applied A level qualification. Where qualifications taken by a student are in the same subject area and similar in content, ‘discounting’ rules have been applied to avoid double counting qualifications.</p><p>[3] Figures are based on final data, except for 2016/17 which is based on revised data.</p><p>[4] The methodology through which student’s ethnicity is identified was changed in 2016/17. Up to 2015/16 a student’s ethnicity was taken from their census record three years prior to the academic year the figures are reported for. In 2016/17 a student’s ethnicity is taken from the census record of their final year of key stage 4 study (normally, three years prior). Due to this change, 2016/17 figures can not be compared to earlier years.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-06-08T13:59:08.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911219/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911219/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911219/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-24","GCE A-level: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Black British students achieved 3 'A' grades or higher in A Levels in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","147796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911220","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Department for Health and Social Care and the Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government is currently listening to stakeholders on their views of what the priorities for this work should be, and working to build the evidence base. We are at a relatively early stage of this piece of work which will complement the Green Paper and will set out our plans once we are clearer on the nature of the output.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-04T16:01:58.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911220/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911220/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911220/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-24","Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, when his Department plans to publish the (a) terms of reference and (b) timescale for the parallel workstream on working-age social care users.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","147824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911221","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-05","<p>Public Health England collect and report information on individuals with foetal alcohol syndrome, however only those identified at birth are notified so it is recognised that this is a significant underestimation of the overall prevalence.</p><p> </p><p>The figures available relate to births in 2012-2016 and cover five regions in England only: the South West, East Midlands and South Yorkshire, Wessex, Thames Valley and the North, including North East and Cumbria, prevalence tables by region and year can be found <a href="http://www.eurocat-network.eu/prevdata/resultsPdf.aspx?title=A5&amp;allanom=false&amp;allregf=true&amp;allrega=true&amp;anomalies=83&amp;winx=1256&amp;winy=677" target="_blank">at</a> the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.eurocat-network.eu/prevdata/resultsPdf.aspx?title=A5&amp;allanom=false&amp;allregf=true&amp;allrega=true&amp;anomalies=83&amp;winx=1256&amp;winy=677" target="_blank">http://www.eurocat-network.eu/prevdata/resultsPdf.aspx?title=A5&amp;allanom=false&amp;allregf=true&amp;allrega=true&amp;anomalies=83&amp;winx=1256&amp;winy=677</a></p><p> </p><p>Rates vary from 0.00 per 10,000 - 0.16 per 10,000 births compared to a European prevalence of 0.54 per 10,000 births.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-05T13:46:58.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911221/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911221/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911221/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-24","Foetal Alcohol Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the number of children born each year in the UK suffering from Foetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","147888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911222","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-08","<p>The Kampala amendments are activated on 17 July 2018. Thereafter, the jurisdiction of the International Criminal Court over the crime of aggression only applies, in the absence of a UN Security Council referral, to acts of aggression committed by States Parties that have ratified or accepted the amendments to the Rome Statute on the crime of aggression. The UK has no plans to ratify these amendments, as we believe that the UN Security Council should be the body responsible for determining when an act of aggression has occurred.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-06-08T10:37:18.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911222/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911222/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911222/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-24","International Criminal Court","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the merits of ratifying the Kampala amendments on the crime of aggression to the Statute of Rome.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","147826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911223","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-05","<p>The Government recognises that Fetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder (FASD) can have a significant impact on the early years development of children and their life chances. Early intervention services can help reduce some of the effects of FASD and prevent some of the secondary disabilities that result. Responsibility for commissioning these services lies with clinical commissioning groups.</p><p> </p><p>The Government remains committed to tackling all alcohol-related harms and is developing a new alcohol strategy. Government officials are currently exploring what should be included in the strategy and aim to publish this early next year following discussions with stakeholders.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-05T13:57:30.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911223/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911223/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911223/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-24","Foetal Alcohol Syndrome","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of NHS services for sufferers of Foetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","147889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911224","Treasury","false","2018-06-04","<p>The performance of PFI and PF2 contracts is monitored by the procuring authority. The government has published a range of advice on managing PFI and PF2 contracts, covering areas such as operational savings, refinancing and termination. HM Treasury assesses and responds to fiscal and financial risks as part of its ongoing business activities.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-04T15:54:15.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911224/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911224/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911224/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what (a) strategic risk management policy and (b)(i) performance management, (ii) financial control and (iii) other processes his Department uses to monitor private finance initiatives.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","147961"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911225","Treasury","false","2018-06-04","HM Treasury and the Infrastructure and Projects Authority publish a range of data on PFI projects including the equity holders for projects where this information has been provided by the procuring authorities. It can be found at this link: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-and-private-finance-2-projects-2017-summary-data.","Newark","Robert Jenrick","147963","2018-06-04T15:50:22.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911225/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911225/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911225/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Carillion: Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has estimated the revenue that Carillion accrued from selling its stake in private finance initiative projects; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","147962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911226","Treasury","false","2018-06-04","HM Treasury and the Infrastructure and Projects Authority publish a range of data on PFI projects including the equity holders for projects where this information has been provided by the procuring authorities. It can be found at this link: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/private-finance-initiative-and-private-finance-2-projects-2017-summary-data.","Newark","Robert Jenrick","147962","2018-06-04T15:50:22.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911226/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911226/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911226/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Carillion: Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what information his Department holds on the jurisdictions in which those companies that purchased Carillion's stakes in private finance initiative projects were registered; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","147963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911227","Treasury","false","2018-06-04","PFI helps to deliver a number of large infrastructure projects critical for the success of the UK economy and the provision of essential public services. The Government continually monitors the financial health of all of its strategic suppliers, including those delivering PFI contracts.","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-04T15:44:47.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911227/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911227/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911227/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Carillion: Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department plans to revise its procedures on monitoring private finance initiatives following the liquidation of Carillion.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","147964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911228","Treasury","false","2018-06-08","<p>Updated guidance was provided in HM Treasury’s Green Book which was published on 6 March 2018.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","147787","2018-06-08T09:47:05.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911228/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911228/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911228/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when his Department plans to publish updated value for money assessment guidance on private finance initiatives.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","147965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911229","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-07","<p>The Department does not collect information about notifications issued to council tax payers. Such matters are the responsibility of local authorities, which administer council tax.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","147833","2018-06-07T16:21:54.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911229/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911229/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-24","Council Tax: Exemptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, with reference to Regulation 10 of the Council Tax Administration and Enforcement Regulations 1992, whether his Department has received reports of local authorities not fulfilling their duty to notify the residents or owners of dwellings which are exempt from council tax.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","147834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911230","Home Office","false","2018-06-22","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The Home Secretary has committed to regularly updating the Home Affairs Select Committee on the results of the Department's review of all removals and immigration detentions, dating back to 2002, of Caribbean nationals now aged over 45 (i.e. born before 1.1.73), to establish whether any could have entered the UK prior to 1973 and therefore might be protected by the 1971 Act.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","147988 ; 147989","2018-06-22T11:53:49.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911230/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911230/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911230/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people who were resident in Ipswich constituency have been deported from the UK since 2011.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","147987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911231","Home Office","false","2018-06-22","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The Home Secretary has committed to regularly updating the Home Affairs Select Committee on the results of the Department's review of all removals and immigration detentions, dating back to 2002, of Caribbean nationals now aged over 45 (i.e. born before 1.1.73), to establish whether any could have entered the UK prior to 1973 and therefore might be protected by the 1971 Act.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","147987 ; 147989","2018-06-22T11:53:49.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911231/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911231/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Deportation: Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of the people deported from Ipswich constituency since 2011 were deemed to be citizens of other Commonwealth countries.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","147988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911232","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>We are aware of an individual case where a former member of Carillion staff has made an enquiry about obtaining new leave to remain on the basis of having obtained employment with a new employer. We have offered a dedicated point of contact in UKVI for the individual or employer to refer to if they need any advice or assistance in submitting a new application</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-04T17:26:25.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911232/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911232/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911232/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Carillion: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what support his Department provides to former Carillion staff who have been asked to reapply for Tier 2 sponsorship since that company went into liquidation.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","147797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911233","Home Office","false","2018-06-22","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The Home Secretary has committed to regularly updating the Home Affairs Select Committee on the results of the Department's review of all removals and immigration detentions, dating back to 2002, of Caribbean nationals now aged over 45 (i.e. born before 1.1.73), to establish whether any could have entered the UK prior to 1973 and therefore might be protected by the 1971 Act.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","147987 ; 147988","2018-06-22T11:53:49.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911233/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911233/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911233/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Deportation: Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of those Commonwealth citizens deported from Ipswich constituency since 2011 are now covered by the Government’s assurances in respect of the Windrush generation.","false","Biography information for Sandy Martin","Ipswich","Sandy Martin","147989"
