"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911267","Home Office","false","2018-06-05","<p>The final timetable for the Offensive Weapons Bill will be announced soon.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-06-05T14:12:31.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911267/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911267/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911267/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Offensive Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when he plans to bring forward legislative proposals for an offensive weapons Bill.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","147931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911268","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes statistics on the number of police officers employed by each Police Force Area in England and Wales on a bi-annual basis. These data are published in the ‘Police workforce, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins.</p><p>Detailed data on the number of officers by rank is collected and published on an annual basis only. The latest data available, covering the situation as at 31 March 2017, can be found in Table_H2 of the data tables accompanying the main release, and can be accessed here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629865/police-workforce-tabs-jul17.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629865/police-workforce-tabs-jul17.ods</a></p><p>The next release of ‘Police workforce’ statistics is due to be published on 19th July, and will represent the picture as at 31 March 2018.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-06-04T15:43:11.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911268/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911268/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911268/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the number of police officers was in England and Wales by rank for the latest date for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911269","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>Our Ambassador in Somalia has spoken to the Governments of Somalia, Puntland and Somaliland to underscore the importance of an immediate cessation of hostilities. Violence is taking place amid an already difficult humanitarian situation and clashes only add to the suffering of people in the area. In speaking to President Muse Bihi (Somaliland) and President Gaas (Puntland) our Ambassador has made clear that economic development, the delivery of better services and an effective response to the region's environmental pressures depend on an enduring cessation of hostilities leading eventually to an agreement underpinning a sustainable peace.</p><p><br>The UK continues to urge sustained, constructive and meaningful dialogue in the region and supports efforts to achieve this.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-04T15:29:50.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911269/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911269/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911269/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-24","Somalia: Somaliland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to support a ceasefire in hostilities between Puntland and Somaliland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911270","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>Our Ambassador has spoken to the Governments of Somalia, Puntland and Somaliland to urge leaders on all sides to commit to an immediate cessation of hostilities, allow humanitarian access to conflict-affected communities and initiate dialogue to reduce tension and avoid miscommunication. The UK has also joined international partners in issuing a statement expressing our concern, which is available at <a href="https://unsom.unmissions.org/somalia%E2%80%99s-international-partners-gravely-concerned-over-clashes-near-tukaraq-call-ceasefire" target="_blank">https://unsom.unmissions.org/somalia%E2%80%99s-international-partners-gravely-concerned-over-clashes-near-tukaraq-call-ceasefire</a>.</p><p>It is imperative that all parties avoid rhetoric or actions that could increase tensions or hostility.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-04T15:31:44.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911270/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911270/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911270/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-24","Somalia: Somaliland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Government of (a) Puntland, (b) Somalia and (c) Swaziland on (i) recent hostilities between Puntland and Somaliland and (ii) threats made by Puntland to Somaliland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911271","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-04","<p>We are very concerned about the plight of the many thousands of people affected by the recent tropical storm in Somaliland in particular and flooding in Somalia more generally. The UK’s early commitment of £45m for the humanitarian response so far in Somalia in 2018 is enabling our bilateral and multilateral partners, such as World Food Programme, UNICEF, Food and Agriculture Organization, OCHA, Islamic Relief, the Somali Red Crescent Society and Save the Children, to be flexible and adapt to urgent needs as they arise. In response to Tropical Storm Sagar, existing NGO and UN partners are drawing on pre-positioned relief supplies and redirecting resources to provide urgently needed water treatment kits, tents, and health and nutrition supplies sufficient to meet the needs of more than 400,000 people in Somaliland and other affected places. The relief effort is continuing, along with assessment work to identify longer term recovery needs.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-04T15:49:06.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911271/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911271/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911271/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-24","Somaliland: Storms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing (a) bilaterally and (b) multilaterally to relief efforts following Cyclone Sagar in Somaliland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911272","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-04","<p>The UK plans to support the delivery of local and parliamentary elections in Somaliland in 2019 by contributing to an audit and update of the voter registration system, providing essential technical expertise for the national election commission, and supporting people with disability to engage in Somaliland’s democratic processes.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-04T15:01:05.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911272/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911272/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911272/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-24","Somaliland: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans her Department has to support Parliamentary elections in Somaliland in 2019.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911273","Home Office","false","2018-06-07","<p>Last year, for the first time, the Home Office collected information on the diversity of those joining fire and rescue services, for 2016/17. This data can be found, broken down by job role in table FIRE1121 here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables#workforce-and-workforce-diversity" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables#workforce-and-workforce-diversity</a></p><p>Data are not available for previous years. The Home Office does not collect data on the number of applications of employment made to each fire service.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","147876","2018-06-07T13:21:57.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911273/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911273/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911273/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Fire and Rescue Services: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications of employment have been made to each fire service from each ethnic group in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","147875"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911274","Home Office","false","2018-06-07","<p>Last year, for the first time, the Home Office collected information on the diversity of those joining fire and rescue services, for 2016/17. This data can be found, broken down by job role in table FIRE1121 here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables#workforce-and-workforce-diversity" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fire-statistics-data-tables#workforce-and-workforce-diversity</a></p><p>Data are not available for previous years. The Home Office does not collect data on the number of applications of employment made to each fire service.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","147875","2018-06-07T13:21:57.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911274/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911274/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911274/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Fire and Rescue Services: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many appointments have been made to each fire service from each ethnic group in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","147876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911275","Home Office","false","2018-06-07","<p>The Home Office does not hold centrally all the information requested.</p><p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on the number of police officers who join the police workforce, as standard direct recruits, broken down by Police Force Area, and the ethnicity of the officer. Data on the ethnicity of standard direct recruits are broken down only into two groups: White or Black and Minority Ethnic.</p><p>Data are published annually in the ‘Police workforce, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins.</p><p>The latest data available, covering joiners up to 2016/17, can be found inthe joiners Open Data Table, which accompanies the main release, here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629367/open-data-table-police-workforce-joiners.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629367/open-data-table-police-workforce-joiners.ods</a></p><p>The Home Office does not collect any data on employment applications made to the police. The next release of ‘Police workforce’ statistics is due to be published on 19th July.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","147878","2018-06-07T13:27:15.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911275/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911275/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911275/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Police: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many employment applications have been made to each police force from each ethnic group in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","147877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911276","Home Office","false","2018-06-07","<p>The Home Office does not hold centrally all the information requested.</p><p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on the number of police officers who join the police workforce, as standard direct recruits, broken down by Police Force Area, and the ethnicity of the officer. Data on the ethnicity of standard direct recruits are broken down only into two groups: White or Black and Minority Ethnic.</p><p>Data are published annually in the ‘Police workforce, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins.</p><p>The latest data available, covering joiners up to 2016/17, can be found inthe joiners Open Data Table, which accompanies the main release, here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629367/open-data-table-police-workforce-joiners.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/629367/open-data-table-police-workforce-joiners.ods</a></p><p>The Home Office does not collect any data on employment applications made to the police. The next release of ‘Police workforce’ statistics is due to be published on 19th July.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","147877","2018-06-07T13:27:15.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911276/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911276/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911276/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Police: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many appointments have been made to each police force from each ethnic group in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","147878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911277","Home Office","false","2018-08-15","<p>The Secretary of State has not received representations from the Equality and Human Rights Commission on the immigration status of members of the Windrush generation in the last 12 months.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-08-15T09:40:15.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911277/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911277/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911277/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Immigration: Windrush Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what representations he has received from the Equality and Human Rights Commission on the immigration status of members of the Windrush generation in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","147879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911278","Treasury","false","2018-06-08","<p>Updated guidance was provided in HM Treasury’s Green Book which was published on 6 March 2018.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","147965","2018-06-08T09:47:05.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911278/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911278/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911278/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when his Department plans to publish updated value for money assessment guidance on private finance initiatives.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911279","Treasury","false","2018-06-08","<p>Updated data on PFI and PF2 projects was published on 29 March 2018.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-08T09:41:41.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911279/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911279/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911279/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when his Department plans to publish updated data on private finance initiative projects on his Department's website.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911280","Treasury","false","2018-06-11","<p>As is normal practice, the government does not comment on taxpayer-specific cases. UK resident PFI contractors, facilities management services and fund management companies, regardless of their shareholders’ registered jurisdiction, will be charged UK corporation tax on profits earned within the UK.</p><p> </p><p>The government is clear that everyone must pay their fair share, and has taken significant steps domestically and internationally to ensure companies pay the right amount of tax.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-11T09:19:05.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911280/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911280/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911280/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the news item on UK PFI and PPP equity offshoring and tax avoidance published by the European Services Strategy Unit, if his Department will make an assessment of the implications for his Department's policies of that Unit's findings that almost half of all private finance initiative projects are majority owned by nine offshore infrastructure funds.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911281","Treasury","false","2018-06-11","<p>The vast majority of PFI projects were signed under the last Labour government – 620, or 86% of all PFI projects in the UK. Since coming to office in 2010, this Government has reformed the approach so that now, PF2 contracts deliver better value for money for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p><p>We have also improved the VfM we get from existing PFI contracts, and this will deliver over £2 billion in efficiencies over the remaining life of the contracts.</p><p> </p><p>The Treasury Green Book is clear that, to compare the costs and benefits that occur at different times between different projects, a discount rate must be applied to the cashflows. This is standard practice in all economic appraisals as it provides a Net Present Cost for the different projects, which enables a proper comparison of the costs and benefits occurring at different times on a consistent basis.</p><p> </p><p>The NAO report’s finding that PF2 costs are around 40 per cent higher than similar projects financed by government borrowing is based on undiscounted cashflows and has not followed the Green Book guidance. It is not, therefore, an appropriate comparison.</p><p> </p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-11T09:13:20.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911281/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911281/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911281/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the report entitled PFI and PF2, published by the National Audit Office on 17 January 2018, what assessment his Department has made of the implications for his Department's policies of that report's findings that PF2 costs are around 40 per cent higher than similar projects financed by government borrowing; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911282","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Home Office does not hold information on either a) the number of boroughs affected and b) the number of cases involving an offender under 18 years.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2018-06-04T15:40:16.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911282/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911282/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911282/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-24","Forensic Science","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the urgent review of 33 cases launched by the Metropolitan Police over suspected mishandling of evidence in the forensic laboratory, what information his Department holds on (a) number of boroughs affected and (b) number of cases involving on offender under 18 years old.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","147897"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911283","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-08","<p>The Government unequivocally condemns attacks on human rights defenders. Our Embassy in Guatemala City monitors the human rights situation in Guatemala closely and embassy staff regularly engage with human rights defenders. Officials participate in the EU's informal human rights monitoring mechanism, the Filter Group, which reviews threats and attacks against human rights defenders and raises concerns with the Guatemalan authorities collectively. They will discuss these cases at the next opportunity.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-06-08T10:47:45.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911283/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911283/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911283/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-24","Guatemala: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in Guatemala on the killing of human rights defenders and community leaders Luis Marroquin, Jose Can Xol and Mateo Chaman Paau this month.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","147820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911284","Treasury","false","2018-06-11","<p>The vast majority of PFI projects were signed under the last Labour government – 620, or 86% of all PFI projects in the UK. Since coming to office in 2010, this Government has reformed the approach so that now, PF2 contracts deliver better value for money for the taxpayer.</p><p>We have improved the VfM we get from existing PFI contracts, and this will deliver over £2 billion in efficiencies over the remaining life of the contracts. In 2012 we also reformed PFI to improve its transparency, and reduce procurement times, through the new PF2 model.</p><p>The Government continually monitors the financial health of all of its strategic suppliers, including those delivering PFI contracts.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-11T09:17:48.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911284/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911284/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911284/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which private finance initiative contracts are being delivered by contractors that his Department deem to be high risk.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911285","Treasury","false","2018-06-11","<p>The Cabinet Office leads on Strategic Supplier Risk Management, and undertakes regular assessments of suppliers. Following Carillion’s profits warning in July, the Treasury was part of the cross government working group, and were fully engaged in the contingency planning process.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-11T09:25:35.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911285/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911285/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911285/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Forty-first report of the Public Accounts Committee, Government risk assessments relating to Carillion, published on 23 May 2018, HC 1045, when his Department first became aware of the Cabinet Office's responses to recommendations to give Carillion a high-risk rating two months before that company collapsed.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911286","Treasury","false","2018-06-08","<p>In line with the practice of successive administrations, details of ministerial discussions are not normally disclosed.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-08T09:43:48.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911286/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911286/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911286/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Carillion: Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what meetings (a) he and (b) Ministers of his Department have held with the Cabinet Office on monitoring private finance Iinitiative contracts held by Carillion.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911287","Treasury","false","2018-06-11","<p>The vast majority of PFI projects were signed under the last Labour government – 620, or 86% of all PFI projects in the UK. Since coming to office in 2010, this Government has reformed the approach so that now, PF2 contracts deliver better value for money for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p><p>We have also improved the VfM we get from existing PFI contracts, and this will deliver over £2 billion in efficiencies over the remaining life of the contracts.</p><p> </p><p>The performance of PFI and PF2 contracts is monitored by the procuring authority. The government has published a range of advice on managing PFI and PF2 contracts, covering areas such as operational savings, refinancing and termination. HM Treasury assesses and responds to fiscal and financial risks as part of its ongoing business activities.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-06-11T09:16:16.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911287/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911287/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/911287/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-24","Private Finance Initiative","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how his Department monitors private finance initiative contracts, including (a) strategic risk management policy, (b) financial control and (c) performance management.","false","Biography information for John McDonnell","Hayes and Harlington","John McDonnell","147794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910111","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-23","<p>DFID provides extensive support to promote more inclusive, open and accountable governance. Last year DFID supported elections in Sierra Leone, Somalia and Kenya. DFID also works with the Westminster Foundation for Democracy in over 30 countries to build trust and participation in democratic institutions, including among minorities and vulnerable groups.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-05-23T14:07:22.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910111/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910111/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910111/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-23","Developing Countries: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","What recent support her Department has provided to strengthen democratic processes and governance in developing countries.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","905510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910112","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-23","<p>It is vital that aid spending delivers value for money. I have set a challenge that we ensure aid money is not just spent well, but cannot be spent better.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2018-05-23T14:07:54.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910112/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910112/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910112/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-23","Overseas Aid: Cost Effectiveness","1","House of Commons","What steps she is taking to promote value for money in aid spending.","false","Biography information for Gordon Henderson","Sittingbourne and Sheppey","Gordon Henderson","905511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910113","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-23","<p>More than 20 million people are experiencing acute food shortages in East Africa. The situation is most severe in Somalia, Ethiopia and South Sudan, with a risk of famine in South Sudan. The UK has recently provided assistance to over 13.6 million people and has allocated £279 million for humanitarian aid to these countries this year.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-05-23T14:08:29.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910113/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910113/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910113/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-23","East Africa: Food Supply","1","House of Commons","What recent assessment she has made of the level of food security in east Africa.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","905513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910114","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-23","<p>Negotiations are still ongoing about the UK’s position following the implementation period. If a UK contribution to EU development funds can best deliver our mutual interests, we should both be open to that. This will be decided on a case by case basis where it represents value for taxpayers’ money.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2018-05-23T14:08:59.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910114/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910114/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910114/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-23","EU Aid","1","House of Commons","What plans her Department has to contribute to EU development and humanitarian funds after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","905515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910164","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Treasure Act 1996 (the Act) and the accompanying Codes of Practice were last fully reviewed in 2001. Many of the recommendations in that review, such as the creation of a Treasure Registry at the British Museum were implemented, and have contributed to the continuing success of the treasure process. The process is under constant review and this, along with outstanding recommendations from 2001, will be reflected in proposals to be set out in the forthcoming public consultation on the Act and the Codes of Practice.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-06-04T13:34:36.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910164/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910164/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910164/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-23","Treasure Act 1996","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, for what reasons there has been no review of the Treasure Act 1998 for thirteen years.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","147293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910165","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-04","<p>The reviewed and revised Treasure Act Code of Practice will be published following a planned public consultation, in accordance with the Treasure Act 1996. The last revised code was published in 2007, and the code is currently under review. We plan to issue a public consultation containing proposals from the review in the coming months.</p><p> </p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-06-04T13:36:11.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910165/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910165/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910165/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-23","Treasure Trove: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when he plans to publish the reviewed Treasure Act Code of Practice; when that code was last reviewed; and what the timetable is for future such reviews.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","147294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910166","Department for Education","false","2018-06-04","<p>We do not hold data on non-levy allocations on a per capita/learner basis.</p><p>The funding system is designed to let employers choose the apprenticeship, training provider and training location that best meet their needs.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-06-04T15:44:12.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910166/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910166/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910166/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-23","Apprentices: Per Capita Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the latest allocation of non-levy apprenticeship funding is on a per capita basis by region.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","147295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910167","Department for Education","false","2018-06-04","<p>The UK remains a highly attractive destination for international students who come to study at our world class universities. We welcome international students, as they make an important contribution to the UK’s higher education sector both economically and culturally. Higher education institutions are autonomous organisations, but the government expects them to handle student complaints seriously, with providers taking into account the needs of all students when developing procedures for the handling of complaints and academic appeals.</p><p> </p><p>The 2017 annual report by the Office of the Independent Adjudicator for Higher Education (OIA) lists the student complaints in England and Wales. It notes that 68% of complaints were made by home students, 6% of complaints were made by EU students and 23% of complaints were made by non-EU students. 3% of complaints were made by students whose status was unknown<em>. </em>The report lists several common factors from cases involving international students. These factors include language barriers and financial concerns. The government continues to work closely with the OIA to understand issues relating to student complaints in higher education.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-06-04T15:53:29.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910167/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910167/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910167/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-23","Overseas Students: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the implications for his Department's policies of the findings of the report by the Office of the Independent Adjudicator for Higher Education of 26 April 2018 on the relative proportion of international students studying in England and Wales who complain about their university’s handling of a grievance compared to home students.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","147343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910168","Department for International Trade","false","2018-06-08","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer given by my Rt Hon. Friend Minister of State for Asia and the Pacific (Mark Field) on 30 April 2018, UIN 136959.</p><p>The UK has a wide-ranging relationship with Thailand on prosperity, education and security issues. My Rt Hon. Friend the Secretary of State for International Trade's visit to Thailand was to set out the future of our bilateral trading relationship and show UK commitment to free trade. Human rights continue to be at the core of our values and we are fully aligned to the Foreign and Commonwealth Office's commitment to raising these issues in the Government's diplomatic engagements overseas. As my Rt Hon. Friend the Secretary of State did in Bangkok, covering the issues that Mr Hall works on, although his specific case was not raised.</p><p>The British Government supports the right of human rights defenders to carry out their work without fear of harassment or reprisals. We also support full implementation of the UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2018-06-08T13:48:07.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910168/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910168/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910168/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-05-23","Andy Hall","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether he has made representations to his Thai counterpart during his recent visit to Thailand on the conviction of human rights activist Andy Hall.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","147395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910169","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-04","<p>The UK is one of the leading humanitarian donors in the Democratic Republic of Congo. Over the last three years, £131m of bilateral UKAid has been provided to support the humanitarian needs in the country. The table below provides a breakdown of disbursements by year.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total (£m)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>31</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>70</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>131</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-04T15:02:23.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910169/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910169/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910169/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-23","Democratic Republic of Congo: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the value is of her Department's humanitarian assistance programmes for the Democratic Republic of Congo in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","147501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910170","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-06-06","<p>Defra’s systems do not differentiate between contractors and other types of contingent worker. As at 31 March 2018, 3 out of 463 contingent workers in Core Defra were on a contracted rate of £1,000 or more per day.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-06-06T16:36:14.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910170/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910170/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910170/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-23","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many contractors currently employed by his Department are paid £1,000 or more per day.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","147405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910171","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-06-04","<p>We do not have any interim contractors currently in role for the department employed on day rate terms of £1,000 or more.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-06-04T15:40:39.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910171/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910171/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910171/answer",,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-05-23","Department for Exiting the European Union: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many contractors currently employed by his Department are paid £1,000 or more per day.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","147406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910172","Department for International Development","false","2018-06-05","<p>DFID do not hold this information. The data relating to contractors pay is not held in a central source. DFID consider there to be a disproportionate cost to provide this information.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-05T14:37:56.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910172/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910172/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910172/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-23","Department for International Development: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many contractors currently employed by her Department are paid £1,000 or more per day.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","147407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910173","Department for International Trade","false","2018-06-06","<p>The Department for International Trade does not employ any contractors on £1000 or more per day.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-06-06T13:15:23.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910173/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910173/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910173/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-05-23","Department for International Trade: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many contractors currently employed by his Department are paid £1,000 or more per day.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","147408"
