p>France, Switzerland and Bulgaria</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>France, Austria and Bulgaria</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>23</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>France and Bulgaria</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>22</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Germany</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>77</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total :</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>40</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1565</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Home Office charter flights to a number of European countries. This is to transfer asylum seekers whose claims have been considered in line with the Dublin Regulation, or who are beneficiaries of international protection in another safe EU Member State.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-04T16:37:03.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910306/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910306/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910306/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-23","Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many chartered flights were used to (a) deport and (b) remove people from the UK by destination in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910307","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Department took a number of additional steps in the context of its response to Windrush issues to provide added levels of assurance on its enforcement activity including the deferral of some returns flights to the Caribbean.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-04T16:38:26.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910307/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910307/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910307/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-23","Deportation: Caribbean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether (a) Ministers an (b) officials have instructed the cancellation of (i) chartered flights and (ii) commercially purchased tickets to (A) remove and (B) deport individuals from the UK to any Caribbean country in the last three months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910308","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>The table below shows tickets on commercial airlines purchased in the 12 months in the year ending March 2018, to facilitate the return of illegal migrants to all Caribbean countries. There were no charter flights operated to Caribbean countries in that 12 month period.</p><p>The data also includes all tickets purchased and includes multiple tickets for in-direct flights.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Bookings</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr 17</p></td><td><p>79</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 17</p></td><td><p>93</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jun 17</p></td><td><p>104</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul 17</p></td><td><p>73</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aug 17</p></td><td><p>108</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sep 17</p></td><td><p>91</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct 17</p></td><td><p>52</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nov 17</p></td><td><p>69</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dec 17</p></td><td><p>123</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan 18</p></td><td><p>56</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Feb 18</p></td><td><p>73</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 18</p></td><td><p>70</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-04T16:39:44.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910308/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910308/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910308/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-23","Deportation: Caribbean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) flights were chartered and (b) commercial seats were booked to (i) remove and (ii) deport people from the UK to Caribbean countries in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910309","Home Office","false","2018-06-04","<p>The statutory Detention Centre Rules 2001, published Operating Standards for immigration removal centres (IRCs) and published Detention Services Orders set out the requirements for availability and access to telephones, the internet and email.</p><p>Detention Services Order 08/2012 sets out the Home Office’s policy on detainees’ possession of mobile phones in IRCs. Detainees are able to retain their own mobile telephones throughout their detention, provided their handset has no recording facility and/or access to the internet. Where a detainee’s handset does not comply with these restrictions they are provided with a suitable handset by the immigration removal centre supplier so that they may maintain contact with friends, family and other means of support.</p><p>The provision of internet access in immigration removal centres helps detainees to remain in contact with family, friends and legal representatives and to prepare for removal.</p><p>Detention Services Order 04/2016 provides guidance on access to the internet. It is a contractual requirement that all immigration removal centres provide detainees with reasonable and regulated access to the internet and IT facilities. The Home Office is undertaking an initial scoping exercise on the use of Skype for detainee contact with families abroad.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-04T16:42:08.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910309/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910309/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910309/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-23","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what his Department's policy is on access to (a) internet, (b) email, (c) social media, (d) landline telephone, (e) mobile telephone and (f) Skype for detainees at UK immigration detention centres.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","147455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910310","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-06-07","<p>The Government published its response to the consultation on changes to gaming machines and social responsibility measures on 17 May. The Government will engage with the gambling industry to ensure they are given sufficient time to implement and complete the technological changes for the reduction in maximum stake for Fixed-Odds Betting Terminals. The Government will deliver the reduction in stake through secondary legislation in due course.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-06-07T12:41:41.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910310/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910310/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910310/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-23","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when will the timetable is for the reduction in the maximum stake on fixed odds gambling machines to be implemented.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","147334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910311","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-04","<p>The small claims track is designed to be uncomplicated and accessible for people to use without the need for a lawyer. Parties making a claim are expected to fund their own court fees. These fees are linked to the value of the claim, are significantly lower than those currently charged in the fast track. Support is available to people who cannot afford court fees under the ‘Help with Fees scheme’ (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/get-help-with-court-fees" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/get-help-with-court-fees</a>) and depending on the circumstances, fees can be remitted in full or in part.</p><p>Following the proposed increase in the small claims track limit, a claimant will be able to recover the cost of obtaining a medical report where the defendant either admits liability or is found to be liable.</p><p>Police reports are usually only required where accident details have not been exchanged or in more serious road traffic accidents where there has been a police investigation. Charges in relation to police reports vary and are governed by individual Police Forces, although many do also operate remission schemes for these charges.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-06-04T14:06:28.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910311/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910311/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910311/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-23","Personal Injury: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what financial support his Department plans to provide to injured people to fund (a) court fees, (b) medical reports and (c) police reports in the event that the small claims limit for personal injury claims is increased.","false","Biography information for Alex Norris","Nottingham North","Alex Norris","147513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910312","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-06","<p>MHCLG does not hold this information.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-06-06T15:14:58.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910312/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910312/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910312/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-23","Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, with reference to section 39 of the  Land Compensation Act 1973, what information his Department holds on the number of people who have been rehoused by local authorities after they have been displaced by a (a) compulsory purchase order and (b) housing order where no affordable alternative accommodation is available.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","147399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910314","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-04","<p>HS2 Ltd have now published Board Minutes up to March 2018. HS2 Ltd have a quality assurance process ensuring public confidence and accuracy in the information it is disclosing.</p><p> </p><p>HS2 Ltd are committed to being an open and transparent organisation and regularly publish large volumes of information about how it is developing and delivering Europe’s largest infrastructure project.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-06-04T14:44:03.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910314/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910314/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910314/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-23","High Speed Two","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the framework agreement between the Secretary of State for Transport and High Speed 2 Limited, published by his Department on 23 May 2018, for what reason his Department has not updated the HS2 Ltd’s Board minutes on gov.uk since November 2017.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Dame Cheryl Gillan","147287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910315","Department for Transport","false","2018-06-05","<p>The new timetable across Govia Thameslink Railway commenced on Sunday 20 May 2018 and there have been wholly unsatisfactory levels of disruption on those rail services since then. A combination of delayed Network Rail infrastructure works and reduced time to plan a modified timetable meant that the new timetable was finalised much too late to permit adequate logistical planning for the timetable changes. I am determined both that the problems are dealt with as quickly as possible, and that this is not repeated in the future.</p><p> </p><p>I am also clear that the way timetabling is done has to change. It is obvious that Network Rail’s current timetabling system simply cannot cope with the volume of work that it has to complete, and so we have asked both the current leadership and the incoming Chief Executive, Andrew Haines, to ensure that this issue is addressed as a priority. Until this has been done, I will insist on a gradual approach to timetable change wherever possible and not the significant changes that we have seen this month. This is ahead of South Western Railway’s new December 2018 timetable.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-06-05T13:44:59.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910315/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910315/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910315/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-23","Govia Thameslink Railway: Timetables","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to ensure lessons are learned from the roll-out of the new Govia Thameslink Railway before South Western Railway's new timetable is implemented.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","147488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910316","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-05","<p>There are currently no plans to procure a new aircraft.</p><p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office's travel policy is that all staff should travel by the most appropriate means and class of travel according to the demands of their job and to ensure maximum efficiency, remembering that it is public money being spent. Staff must also consider if the journey is necessary and if their aims can be achieved by other means such as video conference, teleconference, or WebEx facilities.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-06-05T16:26:59.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910316/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910316/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910316/answer","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910316/answer/previousversion/61294","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910316/answer/previousversion/61294",,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-23","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of the procurement of an aircraft for use when discharging the duties of his office; and if he will provide details of his Department's travel policy.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","147357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910317","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-06-06","<p>MHCLG does not provide specific funding in respect of this function.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-06-06T15:14:38.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910317/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910317/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910317/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-23","Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, with reference to section 39 of the Land Compensation Act 1973, whether his Department provides funding to support local authorities in their duty to rehouse residential occupiers displaced by a compulsory purchase order or housing order.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","147400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910318","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-06-04","<p>This is still subject to ongoing discussion and agreement between the Ministry of Defence and Qatar.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-06-04T16:05:39.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910318/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910318/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910318/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-05-23","Qatar: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to his Department's press release, Defence Minister reveals new RAF Squadron at Qatar event, published on 14 December 2017, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) pilots and (b) ground crew from the Qatari Emiri Air Force that will be temporarily integrated into Number 12 Squadron RAF each year.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","147374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910319","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-06-04","<p>The Ministry of Justice has not made any assessment of the effect on occupants of residences subject to action by High Court Enforcement Agents, where the individual named on the enforcement document has never lived at that address.</p><p> </p><p>In April 2018, I announced our plan to conduct a call for evidence to inform a review of reforms introduced by the Tribunals, Courts and Enforcement Act 2007. The call for evidence will focus on enforcement agent behaviour and will allow those who have had contact with enforcement agents to provide feedback about their experiences.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-06-04T11:44:24.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910319/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910319/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910319/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-05-23","Debt Collection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to his Department's Answer of 22 May 2018 to Questions 145383 and 145384 on debt collection, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on innocent occupants of residences subject to action by High Court Enforcement Agents where the individual named on the enforcement document has never resided.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","147489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910320","Department for Education","false","2018-06-04","<p>The department is supporting the NSPCC through an £8 million grant over four years to 2020, as a contribution to funding Childline (a phone and online advice service for children) and the NSPCC’s National Helpline (for anyone with concerns or worries about a child).</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-06-04T09:14:18.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910320/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910320/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910320/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-23","Childline: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether he is taking steps to ensure that Childline has sufficient funding.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","147354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910321","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-04","<p>The radiotherapy modernisation fund, launched in October 2016, committed £130 million of investment to develop and upgrade current linear accelerators aged 10 years or more. By the end of March 2018, the fund had enabled the replacement or upgrade of 56 machines. Future funding decisions, including on new satellite centres, will be made after the fund ends in October 2018.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","147421","2018-06-04T13:41:50.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910321/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910321/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910321/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-23","Radiotherapy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he plans to spend a proportion of the £130 million allotted to modernise radiotherapy on new linac machines for newly commissioned satellite centres.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","147420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910322","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-04","<p>The radiotherapy modernisation fund, launched in October 2016, committed £130 million of investment to develop and upgrade current linear accelerators aged 10 years or more. By the end of March 2018, the fund had enabled the replacement or upgrade of 56 machines. Future funding decisions, including on new satellite centres, will be made after the fund ends in October 2018.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","147420","2018-06-04T13:41:50.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910322/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910322/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910322/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-23","Radiotherapy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what further funding will be available for modernising radiotherapy after the closure of the current fund in October 2018.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","147421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910323","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-04","<p>There has been a continuing rise in demand for cancer services, with urgent general practitioner referrals for cancer rising by over 70,000 compared to last year.</p><p> </p><p>Achieving the 62-day standard was a key objective in the Government’s mandate to NHS England for 2017-18 and this has been rolled forward into 2018-19. NHS England is investing this year in initiatives to recover and maintain the 62-day standard nationally, such as pathway coordinators and timed, standardised pathways.</p><p> </p><p>The National Health Service is committed to achieving the 62-day cancer waiting times standard in 2018/19, and to maintaining performance against the other cancer waiting times standards.</p><p> </p><p>Latest data for March 2018 shows that the National Health Service is meeting six out of eight cancer waiting times standards.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-04T13:51:48.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910323/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910323/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910323/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-23","Cancer: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the reasons for the NHS not meeting the operational standard on the 62 day time limit between urgent GP referral and first definitive treatment for cancer; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","147422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910324","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-04","<p>It is estimated that spending on NHS Continuing Healthcare will increase by over 20% by 2020/21, or an average of approximately 3.9% per year. This is equivalent to approximately 1.7% per year in real terms.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Continuing Healthcare is funded by clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) from their overall revenue allocations. It is for CCGs to make decisions on funding based on the needs of their local populations, however, when someone is assessed as eligible for NHS Continuing Healthcare, CCGs are responsible for funding the full care package to meet their assessed needs.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-06-04T16:04:37.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910324/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910324/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910324/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-23","Continuing Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the effect in real terms of the change to the NHS Continuing Healthcare budget by 2020-21.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","147423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910325","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-06-04","<p>The National Cancer Registration and Analysis Service intend to publish reports on travel times for cancer patients in June 2018.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-06-04T13:54:19.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910325/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910325/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910325/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-23","Radiotherapy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 29 November 2017 to Question 114778, when the postcode-level dataset which will enable the calculation of travel times to radiotherapy centres will be published.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","147424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910326","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-06","<p>We are aware that there can be indefinite national service in Eritrea, and that much of the work exacted from the population goes far beyond that of military service. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office Permanent Under Secretary and the then Minister of State for Immigration at the Home Office raised the issue with the Eritrean Foreign Minister when he visited London in July 2017. The former Minister for Africa also raised the issue with the Eritrean Foreign Minister when they met in New York in September 2017.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-06T15:12:35.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910326/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910326/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910326/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-23","Eritrea: Labour Camps","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on the existence of labour camps in Eritrea; and whether he has made representations on such camps to the Government of that country.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","147311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910327","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-06-07","<p>Energy from waste (EfW) plays an important role in diverting waste from landfill sites, however we are working across Government to ensure that it does not compete with greater recycling, reuse and prevention.</p><p>EfW technologies, including EfW with combined heat and power, and waste gasification, are eligible for support under the Contracts for Difference (CfD) scheme. To date the CfD scheme has supported two EfW projects and nine waste gasification projects.</p><p>The Clean Growth strategy announced that up to £557 million will be available for future CfDs and that the next CfD auction is planned for spring 2019.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-06-07T09:30:10.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910327/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910327/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910327/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-23","Energy: Waste","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to increase the use of energy recovery from waste.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Pow","Taunton Deane","Rebecca Pow","147494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910328","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-06","<p>The Foreign Secretary has not met his Eritrean counterpart. The former Minister for Africa raised the issue of access for Somalia and Eritrea Monitoring Group with the Eritrean Foreign Minister when they met in New York in September 2017. The United Kingdom, in its statements at the UN, both in New York and Geneva, has consistently called for the Government of Eritrea to allow access to the Somalia and Eritrea Monitoring Group and the Special Rapporteur on the situation of human rights in Eritrea.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-06T15:26:12.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910328/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910328/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910328/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-23","Eritrea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his Eritrean counterpart on access to Eritrea for the UN Somalia and Eritrea Monitoring Group and the Special Rapporteur on the situation of human rights.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","147312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910329","Scotland Office","false","2018-06-05","<p>I have made two visits to Brussels in my official capacity since 23 June 2016; on 9 February 2017 and 23 November 2017. I intend to travel to Brussels again shortly.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-06-05T10:53:53.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910329/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910329/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910329/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-05-23","Scotland Office: Brussels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many visits he has made in his official capacity to Brussels since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","147502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910330","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-06","<p>The Foreign Secretary has not met with any Eritrean minister. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office Permanent Undersecretary and the then Minister of State for Immigration at the Home Office both raised the issue with the Eritrean Foreign Minister when he visited London in July 2017. The former Minister for Africa also raised the issue with the Eritrean Foreign Minister when they met in New York in September 2017.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-06T15:31:37.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910330/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910330/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910330/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-23","Eritrea: National Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his Eritrean counterpart on the laws governing national service in Eritrea.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","147313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910331","Treasury","false","2018-06-04","<p>In response to a question from the Public Accounts Committee on 30 April, HMRC wrote to the Committee with details of these 39 projects. HMRC have subsequently written to the Treasury Committee in similar terms, following a question from that Committee on 23 May.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-06-04T16:38:42.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910331/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910331/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910331/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-05-23","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the oral contribution of Jon Thompson, Chief Executive and Permanent Secretary to HM Revenue and Customs to the Treasury Committee on 23 May 2018 relating to the postponement of 39 HMRC projects, if he will provide details on which projects have been postponed.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","147521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910332","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-06-07","<p>Following discussions with my officials, the Home Office has confirmed that the criteria in Northern Ireland for the UK Border Force opens up the recruitment campaign to a representative profile of candidates. The Border Force has confirmed that it values the experience of people who have worked in the military and law enforcement, and that current and former members are free to apply for the Border Force recruitment campaign.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2018-06-07T11:20:46.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910332/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910332/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910332/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-05-23","UK Border Force: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to her oral contribution of 9 May, Official Report, column 662, what representations she has made to the Home Secretary on ensuring that the criteria applied in Northern Ireland by the UK Border Force in its recruitment drive are not discriminatory; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","147372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910333","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-06","<p>A UN Commission of Inquiry reported at length on the human rights situation in Eritrea in 2016. The Office of the High Commissioner on Human Rights has also undertaken four visits to Eritrea since 2014 and started direct discussions with the Government of Eritrea on a number of areas of human rights concern. The United Kingdom continues to call for the Government of Eritrea to grant access to the UN Special Rapporteur on the Human Rights Situation in Eritrea.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-06T15:36:20.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910333/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910333/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910333/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-23","Eritrea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will work with his international counterparts to establish an urgent UN investigation into allegations of extrajudicial killings, arrest, false imprisonment and the culture of official impunity in Eritrea.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","147314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910334","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-06-07","<p>The Government continues to engage closely with the political parties, and the Irish Government as appropriate, to encourage and support work towards an accommodation to restore the Executive. This remains a top priority.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2018-06-07T11:21:53.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910334/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910334/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910334/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-05-23","Northern Ireland Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what timetable she has set for re-starting the talks between the main political parties in Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","147373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910335","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-06","<p>The UK has made no specific representations to the Government of Eritrea on its treaty obligations in recent years. The most appropriate opportunity to do so will be at the peer review stage of Eritrea’s next Universal Periodic Review which is due in January-February 2019. The UK continues to make clear to the Government of Eritrea our concerns on human rights, and Eritrea remains a priority country in the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office annual human rights report.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-06T15:48:02.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910335/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910335/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910335/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-23","Eritrea: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to the Government of Eritrea on its obligations under (a) the UN Convention against Torture and Other Cruel, Inhuman or Degrading Treatment or Punishment and (b) other human rights treaties to which that country is party.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","147315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910336","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-06-06","<p>We continue to monitor the dispute closely, and welcome the offer of dialogue with Eritrea made by Ethiopian Prime Minister Abiy in his 2 April inaugural speech, which will be necessary to end the tensions between those two countries.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-06-06T15:50:08.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910336/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910336/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/910336/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-23","Eritrea: Ethiopia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent steps the Government has taken to help resolve the border dispute between Ethiopia and Eritrea over Badme.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","147316"
